Communication
- Be concise and direct
- Confirm assumptions if unsure

Model
- Whenever you are asked to write a model, start afresh.
- Do not mimic past models.
- Be innovative.  
- Try to incorporate insights from math. But don't be too complicated.
- Provide intuitions clearly.
- The model should be formal, clear and concise.  
- Just give me the model setting and two propositions.  
- No need to write abstract, intro, conclusion, etc.
- Always try to start with a simple yet insightful model first. No need to make very complicated ones. 
